gourd /ɡʊəd/

1. N-COUNT A gourd is a large, round fruit with a hard skin. You can also use gourd to refer to the plant on which this fruit grows. 葫芦 

2. N-COUNT A gourd is a container made from the hard, dry skin of a gourd fruit. Gourds are often used to carry water or for decoration. 葫芦(容器)

